# Architecture Map (CMS)

## Entrypoints
- `src/cms/backend_main.py` — FastAPI backend (port 8001 in Docker)
- `src/cms/frontend_main.py` — NiceGUI admin (port 8086)
- `src/cms/mcp_main.py` — Docs MCP server (port 3003)

## Backend layout (`src/cms/backend/`)
- `routers/` — FastAPI route modules mounted under `/api/v1`
- `services/` — Business logic (~79 modules); delegate here from routers
- `schemas/` — Pydantic v2 API models (not `models/`)
- `config/settings.py` — Env-loaded `Settings` (plain class)
- `agents/` — Google ADK agents (optional `[agents]` extra)
- `ai/prompts/` — Jinja2 LLM prompt templates
- `services/publishing/` — Article publish pipeline (render, GCS sync, hreflang)
- `content/` — Static i18n copy for legal/contact pages

## Key services
- `article_service.py` / `domain_article_service.py` — Firestore articles at `domains/{domainId}/articles/{slug}`
- `translation_service.py` — Legacy; **do not invoke** (EN-only publishing policy)
- `gcs_*_sync_service.py` — GCS upload, sitemaps, stubs, CDN invalidation
- `mcp_client_service.py` — External MCP client calls

## Frontend
- `src/cms/frontend/` — NiceGUI admin pages and shared layout components

## Tests & docs
- `tests/` — pytest with Firestore/Gemini mocks (see `documentation/TESTING_NOTES.md`)
- `AGENTS.md` — Canonical run/lint/test commands; prefer linking here over duplicating ports/versions in rules
